The unusually red-tinted human cleric struggles again to get out of his stricken position on the floor.  He decides that it's not worth it at this time, and is content with the cool stone.  He rolls onto his back so as to better address his interrogator.<br>
&quot; 'What are these things' you ask? I am not able to completely fulfill your question, but i do know that they appeared out of nowhere. Literally..OUT OF NOWHERE. One minute the monestary is a place of quiet contemplation, a place of safety, and...the next...its infested with beings the likes of which I have never seen.  I...they...it was horrible. Claws..and gaping mouths.  And..and burning red eyes.  But it wasn't the eyes that bothered me. It was the darkness behind them.  The empty void of darkness that lit their demonic faces.  I am certain that they are abominations...nothing like those...things..could be created through the power and the grace of Obad-Hai.......nothing....and they destroyed it. They destroyed all of them....I swear by the quarterstaff of Obad-Hai that I will find these monsters and exact due revenge....oh Suttox......&quot;<br>
The emotionaly drainedl human rolls back onto his stomach and exhales.  It's obvious that he is struggling to deal with so much death in such a short time.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sovbeos>sovbeos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk Man Monster-killa</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 7:40:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffaeryfirealongthenightshorefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/sovbeos/stance.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Comfort</span><hr size=1> Serin quickly moves over to Toric to provide him some support, and a friendly hand he can touch.<br>
