D--> oints toward pedestal:: when it happened.  If it really was meant as protection, it was definitely triggered as a means of a last resort.  By that time, the battle would have been a lost cause.  However, the sound of combat still raged on, even with me trapped.  However, at some point, I began to hear a strangely eerie, soothing melody.  It seemed almost like a lament, or a farewell melody exchanged between lovers.  It was very enchanting.  Then I heard the grating of stone on stone in front of me.  Finally, there was a huge blast.  It shook the ground I stood on.  Then...silence.  Except that it wasn't silent, because i could hear a faint clicking...and a sound that reminded me of the clicking of my own breastplate armor as I am running.  Then there was nothing.  Nothing until you arrived.  Thank you once more.  You rescued me from a certainly long and painful death.  I am endebted to you.  All of you.  Now...about the box.  I have no grasp of what could possibly be contained, and what the monks were protecting, but I DO know that they went to a lot of trouble to protect it.  As far as actually opening it goes, I see no reason why you shouldn't let your own heart decide that.  I personally have no reason to look further.  Although it may contain some potent magic or even some clue as to why this place of solitude was disturbed by such evil forces.  No, I am through with the box.  I have protected it. And at the loss of my new friends.  These people who supported me in my time of chaos.  And now it's over. I've protected the box. My promise is fulfilled.&quot;<br>
